#: ../../../docs/lexers.rst:5
msgid "Available lexers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/lexers.rst:7
msgid "This page lists all available builtin lexers and the options they take."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/lexers.rst:9
msgid "Currently, **all lexers** support these options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/lexers.rst:11
msgid "`stripnl`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/lexers.rst:12
msgid "Strip leading and trailing newlines from the input (default: ``True``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/lexers.rst:14
msgid "`stripall`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/lexers.rst:15
msgid ""
"Strip all leading and trailing whitespace from the input (default: "
"``False``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/lexers.rst:18
msgid "`ensurenl`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/lexers.rst:19
msgid ""
"Make sure that the input ends with a newline (default: ``True``).  This is "
"required for some lexers that consume input linewise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/lexers.rst:24
msgid "`tabsize`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/lexers.rst:25
msgid "If given and greater than 0, expand tabs in the input (default: ``0``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/lexers.rst:27
msgid "`encoding`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/lexers.rst:28
msgid ""
"If given, must be an encoding name (such as ``\"utf-8\"``). This encoding "
"will be used to convert the input string to Unicode (if it is not already a "
"Unicode string). The default is ``\"guess\"``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/lexers.rst:32
msgid ""
"If this option is set to ``\"guess\"``, a simple UTF-8 vs. Latin-1 detection "
"is used, if it is set to ``\"chardet\"``, the `chardet library <https://"
"chardet.github.io/>`_ is used to guess the encoding of the input."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/lexers.rst:40
msgid ""
"The \"Short Names\" field lists the identifiers that can be used with the "
"`get_lexer_by_name()` function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/lexers.rst:43
msgid "These lexers are builtin and can be imported from `pygments.lexers`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/lexers.rst:0
msgid "Short names"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/lexers.rst:0
msgid "Filenames"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/lexers.rst:0
msgid "MIME types"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/lexers.rst:49
msgid "Iterating over all lexers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/lexers.rst:53
msgid ""
"To get all lexers (both the builtin and the plugin ones), you can use the "
"`get_all_lexers()` function from the `pygments.lexers` module:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/lexers.rst:57
msgid ""
">>> from pygments.lexers import get_all_lexers\n"
">>> i = get_all_lexers()\n"
">>> i.next()\n"
"('Diff', ('diff',), ('*.diff', '*.patch'), ('text/x-diff', 'text/x-patch'))\n"
">>> i.next()\n"
"('Delphi', ('delphi', 'objectpascal', 'pas', 'pascal'), ('*.pas',), ('text/x-"
"pascal',))\n"
">>> i.next()\n"
"('XML+Ruby', ('xml+ruby', 'xml+erb'), (), ())"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/lexers.rst:68
msgid ""
"As you can see, the return value is an iterator which yields tuples in the "
"form ``(name, aliases, filetypes, mimetypes)``."
msgstr ""
